ttps:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Apple_TV\\\">Apple TV<\\/a>\\u00a0digital media players,\\u00a0<a style=\\\"color: #3366cc; background: none; overflow-wrap: break-word;\\\" title=\\\"Software\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software\\\">software<\\/a>, and both Apple-branded and selected third-party accessories.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The first Apple Stores were originally opened as two locations in May 2001 by then-<a class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" style=\\\"color: #3366cc; background: none; overflow-wrap: break-word;\\\" title=\\\"CEO\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/CEO\\\">CEO<\\/a>\\u00a0<a style=\\\"color: #3366cc; background: none; overflow-wrap: break-word;\\\" title=\\\"Steve Jobs\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Steve_Jobs\\\">Steve Jobs<\\/a>, after years of attempting but failing\\u00a0<a style=\\\"color: #3366cc; background: none; overflow-wrap: break-word;\\\" title=\\\"Store-within-a-store\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Store-within-a-store\\\">store-within-a-store<\\/a>\\u00a0concepts. Seeing a need for improved retail presentation of the company\'s products, he began an effort in 1997 to revamp the retail program to get an improved relationship with consumers and hired\\u00a0<a style=\\\"color: #3366cc; background: none; overflow-wrap: break-word;\\\" title=\\\"Ron Johnson (businessman)\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Ron_Johnson_(businessman)\\\">Ron Johnson<\\/a>\\u00a0in 2000. Jobs relaunched Apple\'s online store in 1997 and opened the first two physical stores in 2001. The media initially speculated that Apple would fail, but its stores were highly successful, bypassing the sales numbers of competing nearby stores and within three years reached\\u00a0<a style=\\\"color: #3366cc; background: none; overflow-wrap: break-word;\\\" title=\\\"United States dolla